Satellite Earth exploration (active) services and space research (active) services operating in the 13.25-13.4 GHz frequency band of 5.498A shall not cause harmful interference to aviation radio navigation services, or restrict their use and development. (WRC-97) 5.499 Additional Allocation: In Bangladesh and India, the 13.25-14 GHz frequency band is also allocated to fixed services as the main business. In Pakistan, the 13.25-13.75 GHz frequency band is allocated to fixed services as the main business. (WRC-12) 5.499A satellite fixed service (air to ground) uses the 13.4-13.65 GHz frequency band limited to geostationary satellite systems and must reach an agreement with the Space Research Service (air-to-air) satellite system that relays data from space stations in geostationary satellite orbit to relevant space stations in non geostationary satellite orbit, in accordance with Article 9.21, as of November 27, 2015. （WRC-15）
5.499B The competent authority shall not hinder the deployment and operation of satellite standard frequency and time signals (ground to air) with secondary business divisions in the 13.4-13.65 GHz frequency band due to the primary business division status of FSS (air to ground). （WRC-15）
The division of space research services as the main business of 5.499C in the 13.4-13.65 GHz frequency band is limited to: - Space research service (air-to-air) satellite systems that relay data from space stations in geostationary satellite orbit to relevant space stations in non geostationary satellite orbit, as of November 27, 2015, for which the Radio Communication Bureau has received its pre published information;
- Active onboard sensors;
A space research service (air to ground) satellite system that relays data from a space station in geostationary satellite orbit to relevant earth stations.
